  <div class="container">
    <article>
      <div class="space gap-top"></div>
      <section class="row">
        <div class="one third padded">
          <a href="./sass-compass">
            <div class="large circle"><div class="blue-3 cell"><i class="icon-plus-sign-alt"></i></div></div>
            <h1 class="align-center">Built with Sass &amp; Compass</h1>
          </a>
          <p class="pad-left pad-right">GroundworkCSS has been built from the ground up with the incredibly powerful CSS preprocessor, Sass. Sass is an extension of CSS3, adding nested rules, variables, mixins, selector inheritance, and more. Itâ€™s translated to well-formatted, standard CSS using the command line tool or a web-framework plugin.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="one third padded">
          <a href="./components">
            <div class="large circle"><div class="red cell"><i class="icon-laptop"></i></div></div>
            <h1 class="align-center">Flexible &amp; Responsive</h1>
          </a>
          <p class="pad-left pad-right">GroundworkCSS offers the most advanced responsive layout techniques in the world. Featuring an incredibly flexible, nestable, fluid grid system: the GroundworkCSS grid system supports any columns in any fractional amount from halves to twelfths. The result is a framework that works for virtually any imaginable modern layout.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="one third padded">
          <a href="https://github.com/groundworkcss/groundwork" target="_blank">
            <div class="large circle"><div class="green cell"><i class="icon-github-alt"></i></div></div>
            <h1 class="align-center">Free &amp; Open-Source</h1>
          </a>
          <p class="pad-left pad-right">GroundworkCSS is open-source, hosted on Github and 100% free. GroundworkCSS was created by Gary Hepting, Sr. Front-End Engineer at SideReel, to make responsive development and rapid responsive prototyping a breeze.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <hr class="gapped" />
      <div class="row">
        <div class="one whole pad-left">
          <h2>Why Use GroundworkCSS?</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <section class="row">
        <div class="one half">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="three small-tablet fourths right-one padded">
              <h3>The Last Grid You'll Ever Need</h3>
              <p>GroundworkCSS's flexible grid system enables you to do rapid development and scales to fit any screen size, from handheld devices to large format televisions.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="one small-tablet fourth left-three padded align-center">
              <a href="./grid"><div class="large square"><div class="green rounded cell"><i class="icon-th"></i></div></div></a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="one half">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="three small-tablet fourths right-one padded">
              <h3>Device Agnostic</h3>
              <p>The grid allows you to quickly and easily adapt page layouts for mobile devices as well as the desktop and enables you to build one site that looks great on virtually any device.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="one small-tablet fourth left-three padded align-center">
              <a href="./grid"><div class="large square"><div class="navy rounded cell"><i class="icon-mobile-phone"></i></div></div></a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
